704932f-a.title: Brooklyn: Hicks Street - Remsen Street
704932f-a.text:
Hicks Street, west side, south of Remsen Street. The corner building
is the William G. Low howe, and beyond it is the Grace (P.E.) Church.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

706457f-a.title: Brooklyn: Remsen Street - Hicks Street
706457f-a.text:
Remsen Street, west from Hicks Street to the East River.
April 7, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

706458f-a.title: Brooklyn: Remsen Street - Hicks Street
706458f-a.text:
Remsen Street, east of Hicks Street, showing in the center, the home
of John A. Latimer (No. 63), who was an accountant for the Brooklyn Savings
Bank in 1876.
About 1900.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

706459f-a.title: Brooklyn: Remsen Street - Hicks Street
706459f-a.text:
7179 Remsen Street, north side, between Hicks and Henry Streets,
showing the Thomas Sullivan residence (No. 77), facing the street lamp.
(Se was president of the Brooklyn City R.R. Co. for many years).
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
